 office opens at eight.","translation":"Kantor buka pukul delapan.","synonym":"workplace","antonym":"home"},{"id":"w1d3-internship","word":"internship","meaning":"magang","pronunciation":"internship","phonetic":"/ˈɪntɜːrnʃɪp/","partOfSpeech":"noun","example":"My internship teaches me new skills.","translation":"Magang saya mengajarkan keterampilan baru.","synonym":"placement","antonym":"unemployment"},{"id":"w1d3-project","word":"project","meaning":"proyek","pronunciation":"project","phonetic":"/ˈprɒdʒekt/","partOfSpeech":"noun","example":"We are working on a new project.","translation":"Kami sedang mengerjakan proyek baru.","synonym":"assignment","antonym":"idleness"},{"id":"w1d3-meeting","word":"meeting","meaning":"rapat","pronunciation":"meeting","phonetic":"/ˈmiːtɪŋ/","partOfSpeech":"noun","example":"The meeting starts at nine.","translation":"Rapat dimulai pukul sembilan.","synonym":"conference","antonym":"separation"},{"id":"w1d3-report","word":"report","meaning":"laporan","pronunciation":"report","phonetic":"/rɪˈpɔːrt/","partOfSpeech":"noun","example":"I write a report every Friday.","translation":"Saya menulis laporan setiap Jumat.","synonym":"document","antonym":"silence"}],"grammar":{"id":"g1d3","title":"Subject Pronouns","level":"Basic","function":"Subject pronouns replace the person or thing doing the action.","formula":"I, you, we, they, he, she, it","positive":"She works in an office.","negative":"They are not late.","question":"Is he your supervisor?","explanation":"Choose a pronoun that matches the subject.","commonMistake":"Do not use an object pronoun such as “me” as the subject.","miniExample":"She works in an office."}},{"day":4,"title":"Day 4","vocabulary":[{"id":"w1d4-breakfast","word":"breakfast","meaning":"sarapan","pronunciation":"breakfast","phonetic":"/ˈbrekfəst/","partOfSpeech":"noun","example":"I eat breakfast at seven.","translation":"Saya sarapan pukul tujuh.","synonym":"morning meal","antonym":"fasting"},{"id":"w1d4-lunch","word":"lun